to trouble sooner or later.

14:22.230 --> 14:24.028
My guess is sooner.

14:24.670 --> 14:25.740
[SCATTING]

14:27.670 --> 14:30.708
# I like the bear barking up on top #

14:30.870 --> 14:33.385
# Beat of the rhythm like
it's never gonna stop #

14:33.470 --> 14:34.540
[TRAILS OFF]

14:35.990 --> 14:39.779
[GROWLS SOFTLY] That boy is really
starting to steam my clams.

14:39.870 --> 14:42.066
Say, isn't he old enough to take the post?

14:42.150 --> 14:45.780
Yeah he is, Floyd,
but he just doesn't take it seriously.

14:45.950 --> 14:48.306
Not since that thing fell out of the sky.

14:48.390 --> 14:50.700
Now it's all rock this and roll that.

14:50.790 --> 14:53.146
- And some guy named Dingus.
- Yeah,

14:53.230 --> 14:55.187
I guess I was a little like that
at his age.

14:55.350 --> 14:57.103
Had no interest in being a barber.

14:57.190 --> 14:59.386
Had my heart set on astrophysics.

14:59.630 --> 15:03.544
That is until my dad
showed me... The Book.

15:03.710 --> 15:05.667
- The Book?
- Hang on a sec.

15:13.590 --> 15:16.230
The Book. Real pictures of what can happen

15:16.310 --> 15:18.347
if sheep go too long without grooming.

15:18.630 --> 15:22.146
KHAMPA: Huh... Huh!

15:23.430 --> 15:25.023
[KHAMPA GASPS]

15:25.230 --> 15:28.268
- Tell me when you've seen enough.
- [EXCLAIMS]

15:28.350 --> 15:30.467
Yep, one look at this scared me straight.

15:30.550 --> 15:33.145
I began my apprenticeship the next day
and never looked back.

15:33.230 --> 15:37.349
"Scared straight." Huh.
Maybe that's what Bodi needs.

15:37.550 --> 15:39.940
- Hey, you wanna borrow The Book?
- No, Floyd.

15:40.270 --> 15:42.660
I think I've got a better idea.

15:43.630 --> 15:45.861
[GUITAR MUSIC PLAYING]

15:51.790 --> 15:54.624
KHAMPA: Bodi! Bodi! Open this door, son!

15:54.710 --> 15:56.588
- [BODI GRUNTING]
- KHAMPA: Oh, no, you don't!

15:56.670 --> 15:58.866
BODI: I can't help it, Dad.
The music's in me. It's in me!

15:58.950 --> 16:02.785
Angus says it's like a fever
that takes hold and never lets you go.

16:03.030 --> 16:04.146
You disappoint me, son.

16:04.430 --> 16:05.546
Okay, this is your post.

16:06.470 --> 16:08.541
Get used to it. See you at dawn.

16:08.630 --> 16:10.622
- Sunrise?
- Yes! Dawn! Sunrise!

16:10.710 --> 16:11.939
First thing in the morning!

16:12.030 --> 16:14.909
- End of the night! Come on!
- Oh. Okay.

16:16.950 --> 16:18.384
[SIGHS]

16:23.910 --> 16:24.900
[LAUGHING]

