16:33.190 --> 16:34.943
KHAMPA: Shh. Settle down guys,
it's me. It's me!

16:35.030 --> 16:36.066
- See?
- [SHEEP PANTING]

16:36.630 --> 16:38.428
Why are you dressed up like a wolf?

16:38.550 --> 16:41.304
Wow, seriously?
You've all forgotten the plan?

16:42.030 --> 16:43.783
I specifically picked you three

16:43.870 --> 16:45.589
because you're the best and the brightest.

16:45.670 --> 16:46.945
- Yeah, for sheep.
- Aah!

16:47.030 --> 16:48.703
All right, just put these on.

16:51.150 --> 16:52.220
SHEEP: Hey, look.

16:52.510 --> 16:54.308
- Wolf's eating my head.
- [LAUGHING]

16:54.390 --> 16:55.790
KHAMPA: There's nothing funny about that.

16:55.870 --> 16:57.987
Okay, Bodi's in position.

16:58.190 --> 17:01.706
On my signal,
we give him the scare of his life.

17:06.230 --> 17:07.505
That was the signal.

17:08.030 --> 17:12.023
[SHEEP PANTING]

17:17.390 --> 17:19.426
[ALL GRUNTING, SCREAMING]

17:19.550 --> 17:21.826
[GROWLING, GNAWING]

17:23.589 --> 17:25.104
[GUITAR MUSIC PLAYING]

17:32.270 --> 17:34.501
- [GROANS]
- Huh? Oh!

17:34.590 --> 17:36.661
Wolf! [GASPING]

17:43.750 --> 17:45.309
Wolf! Wolf! [SCREAMING]

17:45.390 --> 17:47.905
KHAMPA: Whoa, whoa, whoa! Guys! It's me!

17:48.510 --> 17:49.660
[SHEEP GROUP SCREAMING]

17:51.190 --> 17:53.227
The wolves are coming!
The wolves are coming!

17:53.310 --> 17:55.063
Shut your windows! Lock your doors!

17:56.030 --> 17:57.066
Wolf!

17:57.990 --> 17:59.709
[GRUNTING, SCREAMING]

18:01.790 --> 18:04.749
BODI: Everybody, listen up!
The wolves are coming!

18:05.070 --> 18:06.424
[SHEEP SCREAMING]

18:09.510 --> 18:10.500
[GROANS]

18:18.070 --> 18:19.140
[SHEEP SCREAMING]

18:19.750 --> 18:22.219
Get outta there, you chowderhead!
Come here!

18:23.870 --> 18:26.624
- Take that, you ding-busted wolf!
- Aah!

18:26.790 --> 18:29.225
The wolves! They're here! They're coming!

18:29.750 --> 18:31.867
- SHEEP 1: Help.
- SHEEP 2: Help. Help. Please, help.

18:31.950 --> 18:34.146
Stay back. I'm dangerous. [GRUNTS]

18:34.230 --> 18:35.266
SHEEP 1: Please help!

18:45.110 --> 18:46.146
[SHEEP SCREAMING]

18:47.230 --> 18:48.266
No!

18:51.190 --> 18:52.863
[SHEEP EXCLAIMING]

18:55.590 --> 18:56.626
[GRUNTING]

18:59.230 --> 19:00.710
[GASPS]

19:02.310 --> 19:04.461
[FIREWORKS CRACKLING]

19:12.150 --> 19:13.903
[SHUDDERING, PANTING]

19:19.990 --> 19:21.982
Well, all things considered,
it could have been a lot worse.

19:22.070 --> 19:23.902
- Oh, yeah.
- Yeah, kind of embarrassing,

19:23.990 --> 19:27.586
getting fooled by those
cockamamie wolf getups. [LAUGHS]

19:27.670 --> 19:31.550
Where'd Khampa get the notion
to do a crazy thing like that, anyway?

19:33.710 --> 19:35.667
Hello, Khampa. How's things?

19:36.790 --> 19:38.144
[GROWLS SOFTLY]

19:42.150 --> 19:43.869
Shot of wheatgrass, Sam.

19:44.430 --> 19:47.548
[GROANS] Ah, heck, make it a double.

19:48.030 --> 19:49.828
- [GLASSES CLINK]
- You want to talk about it?

19:49.950 --> 19:51.543
Don't pin this one on me, Fleet.

19:51.630 --> 19:53.701
If he'd been doing his job
guarding the village...

19:53.790 --> 19:55.110
I thought that was your job.

19:55.550 --> 19:57.781
Well, yeah, it is my job,
but I wasn't doing my job.

19:57.870 --> 19:58.906
[EXHALES LOUDLY]

19:59.110 --> 20:01.147
I think you've established that.

20:02.230 --> 20:05.906
Bodi isn't you. He wants to go.

20:05.990 --> 20:07.185
Well, that's just crazy talk.

20:07.270 --> 20:09.626
Who else is gonna guard this place
after I'm gone?

20:09.710 --> 20:11.508
From what? The wolves?

20:12.030 --> 20:16.149
Maybe you're sitting up there waiting
for something that's never coming back.

20:16.350 --> 20:17.830
What if they do, Fleet?

20:17.910 --> 20:19.549
Okay, what if they do?

20:19.630 --> 20:22.782
You think Bodi's gonna be able
to protect the village?

20:24.470 --> 20:27.190
He is who he is.

20:29.630 --> 20:32.509
He's looking for his own paradise.

20:36.030 --> 20:37.066
##

20:46.630 --> 20:48.110
[SIGHS]

21:21.030 --> 21:22.259
BODI: Dad?

21:22.350 --> 21:25.582
Just wanted to let
you know I'm ready to...

21:30.910 --> 21:31.900
What's this?

21:33.150 --> 21:34.584
Go to the city.

21:35.150 --> 21:37.745
But if you fail, you come back.

21:37.830 --> 21:40.425
And you never speak of music again.

21:41.630 --> 21:42.700
Okay.

21:55.950 --> 21:57.464
[SIGHS QUIETLY]

22:05.550 --> 22:07.746
Well, keep those shears sharp, Floyd.

22:07.830 --> 22:09.184
Come back and see us sometime, huh?

22:09.270 --> 22:11.865
- Hey.
- Carl. Stay clean.

22:13.230 --> 22:14.459
- Put 'er there, Bodi.
- Ow! [LAUGHS]

22:14.550 --> 22:15.950
- [STATIC CRACKLES]
- [LAUGHS]

22:17.150 --> 22:20.860
You got me good, Steve.
I'm really gonna miss that.

22:22.950 --> 22:28.867
I um... I got a little something for you.
Now where'd I put it?

22:37.750 --> 22:38.979
SHEEP: Nice!

22:41.630 --> 22:43.349
FLEETWOOD: This is your life.

22:46.550 --> 22:48.348
Make it a happy one.

22:53.710 --> 22:55.383
[WIND WHOOSHING]

23:02.750 --> 23:03.786
SHEEP GROUP: Bye!

23:04.750 --> 23:06.104
See you later, Bodi.

23:17.310 --> 23:18.949
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

23:20.790 --> 23:21.860
##

23:22.830 --> 23:24.105
RIFF: I think I got something!

23:24.430 --> 23:27.025
Hey, Skozz! Get Linnux on the line!

23:27.430 --> 23:28.625
[PANTING]

23:29.950 --> 23:32.306
That's right. Both kneecaps.

23:32.390 --> 23:34.347
Yeah, really give it to him.

23:34.430 --> 23:38.265
- Okay, gotta go. Bye, Mom.
- [PHONE BEEPS]

23:39.270 --> 23:43.184
Can we get a red cord
to go with the red phone?

23:43.350 --> 23:44.340
Come on!

23:44.430 --> 23:45.784
Riff, you're bothering me.

23:45.870 --> 23:49.022
We got movement up here!
One of the mastiffs is heading out.

23:49.110 --> 23:52.148
What? A mastiff is leaving Snow Mountain?

23:52.230 --> 23:53.505
- [GASPS]
- [GLASS SHATTERS]

23:54.270 --> 23:55.784
[RIFF OVER PHONE]
I think it's the big guy's kid.

23:55.870 --> 23:58.305
I hate the big guy.

23:58.630 --> 24:00.144
What about the rest of the army?

24:00.230 --> 24:03.621
Uh, checking.
Checking. Checking. Checking.

24:03.750 --> 24:05.423
No, nothing. They're staying put.

24:05.910 --> 24:07.390
You want us to take this guy out?

24:07.630 --> 24:09.064
- 'Cause I'll take this guy out.
- LINNUX: [OVER PHONE] No.

24:09.150 --> 24:11.426
- It'll be done in two seconds.
- LINNUX: No.

24:11.510 --> 24:12.546
Okay. Whoa, whoa!

24:12.990 --> 24:15.664
He's getting on the bus.
He's getting on the bus!

24:15.750 --> 24:18.390
LINNUX: Well, why are you
still talking to me?

24:18.510 --> 24:20.661
Don't let him out of your sight!
Bring him to me.

24:21.110 --> 24:25.229
We get him, we get Snow Mountain. [LAUGHS]

24:25.630 --> 24:29.465
Get your suit and tie on, Skozz,
we are out of here! Whoo-hoo!

24:30.470 --> 24:32.780
##

25:07.350 --> 25:08.386
[SHIVERS]

25:10.470 --> 25:12.701
Thanks very much for the bus ride!

25:12.790 --> 25:15.589
Oh, hey, do you know where I can find
Rock 'n' Roll Park?

25:15.670 --> 25:17.229
Oh, okay. Good talk.

25:17.350 --> 25:18.500
[WOMAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY OVER PA]

25:18.590 --> 25:20.149
Hi there. Pardon me.

25:20.230 --> 25:21.903
I'm just into town,
and I'm looking for a place...

25:22.030 --> 25:23.987
Right on time.

25:28.070 --> 25:29.106
[STRUGGLING]

25:30.150 --> 25:33.939
RIFF: We're gonna nail him from above,
so he don't see us coming.

25:35.030 --> 25:37.784
I reel him in, you knock him out.

25:37.870 --> 25:39.668
Okay, give me a hand.

25:39.870 --> 25:40.906
[BOTH GRUNTING]

25:41.430 --> 25:43.581
Okay. Flip your side around.

25:44.590 --> 25:46.468
No, the other way.

25:46.630 --> 25:50.465
No, not you, Skozz.
Come on, man, we don't got time for this.

25:50.630 --> 25:52.986
All right, all right, let's roll.

25:53.150 --> 25:55.187
WOMAN: [OVER PA] Passenger Lawrence Gan,

25:55.390 --> 25:58.542
please report to the supervisor's office
immediately, thank you.

25:59.030 --> 26:00.430
[RIFF CHUCKLING]

26:00.510 --> 26:02.820
- Yeah, I got you now, mastiff.
- [SCOPE BEEPING]

26:03.390 --> 26:06.622
- Hold it steady, Skozz. Ready.
- [MACHINE POWERING UP]

26:06.710 --> 26:07.985
Aim.

26:08.590 --> 26:09.626
Fire!

26:10.470 --> 26:14.350
- Whoa! Grab my feet, Skozz!
- [CRASHING]

26:14.430 --> 26:16.467
Sir, do you know
where Rock 'n' Roll Park is?

26:17.750 --> 26:19.707
[CAR ALARM BLARING]

26:20.030 --> 26:21.066
##

26:24.830 --> 26:26.059
Oh!

27:00.950 --> 27:02.270
[HORN HONKING]

27:04.230 --> 27:05.220
Hi!

27:06.590 --> 27:08.547
Hey, do you know where I can find
Rock 'n' Roll Park?

27:08.630 --> 27:11.145
- [ENGINE REVVING]
- [SCREAMING]

27:11.230 --> 27:12.664
Oh! Whoa!

27:12.990 --> 27:14.504
- ANIMAL: Watch it!
- [CROWD SCREAMING]

27:15.710 --> 27:16.985
- Whoa!
- [TRAIN HORNS HONKING]

27:18.790 --> 27:20.019
Whoa!

27:22.470 --> 27:23.870
[GRUNTS]

27:25.470 --> 27:27.063
[BLUES MUSIC PLAYING IN THE DISTANCE]

27:57.270 --> 27:58.989
[REGGAE MUSIC PLAYING]

28:01.030 --> 28:02.020
[PUNK MUSIC PLAYING]

28:06.510 --> 28:08.467
[JAZZ MUSIC PLAYING]

28:11.830 --> 28:13.423
[RAP MUSIC PLAYING]

28:24.070 --> 28:25.789
Whoa! Whoa!

28:25.870 --> 28:26.940
Oh, boy.

28:27.030 --> 28:31.468
Do not look over there,
but we got a nutjob at 12 o'clock.

28:31.550 --> 28:34.588
- Oh, I just looked over there.
- I told you not to look over there.

28:34.670 --> 28:36.901
I know you did, but when you tell me that,
it makes me want to look.

28:36.990 --> 28:39.459
Do you know what this means? This is fate!

28:39.550 --> 28:41.348
Just like Mr. Scattergood!

28:41.470 --> 28:43.587
Sorry, Angus Scattergood?

28:43.670 --> 28:44.865
Yes! Yes!

28:44.950 --> 28:47.260
Mr. Scattergood came to Rock 'n' Roll Park

28:47.350 --> 28:51.230
and found a band in need
of a guitar player just like you!

28:51.310 --> 28:53.142
This is unreal!

28:53.510 --> 28:56.105
Sorry I'm late, dudes.

28:57.950 --> 29:00.306
[STUTTERS] Uh, who's the dog?

29:00.390 --> 29:03.189
I'm Bodi. I'm your new guitar player.

29:03.870 --> 29:05.145
Oh!

29:05.230 --> 29:09.907
Oh, cool. I like that. Okay.
Yeah, you're the new... guitar player.

29:09.990 --> 29:11.629
- Well, [SCOFFS] welcome to the band.
- Yes!

29:12.950 --> 29:15.749
Oh. Uh, incidentally,
doesn't he have to do

29:15.830 --> 29:17.344
some kind of auditional thing first?

29:17.430 --> 29:19.308
Or am I mistaken?

29:19.390 --> 29:21.621
- Oh, Trey...
- Well, it's just a formality, really.

29:21.710 --> 29:24.430
Just a little thing we call a "shred-off."

29:24.590 --> 29:25.580
PIG: Shred-off?

29:25.670 --> 29:27.184
TREY:
Yeah, we're gonna have a little shred-off!

29:27.270 --> 29:29.227
- [CROWD EXCLAIMING, CHEERING]
- CROWD: Shred-off!

29:29.470 --> 29:32.941
[CROWD CHANTING] Shred-off! Shred-off!

29:33.030 --> 29:34.225
What's a shred-off?

29:34.310 --> 29:36.905
Who wants to tell him what a shred-off is?
Well, why don't I tell you?

29:36.990 --> 29:39.027
A shred-off is just a little thing
where you play a lick,

29:39.110 --> 29:42.103
and then I get to play a lick
and then you get to be in the band.

29:42.190 --> 29:43.624
[LAUGHS] That sounds fun!

29:43.750 --> 29:44.786
You betcha!

29:45.590 --> 29:48.947
- [SIGHS]
- [DRUM BEATS PLAYING]

29:51.590 --> 29:53.388
[GUITAR MUSIC PLAYING]

30:39.990 --> 30:41.390
[CROWD CHEERING]

30:49.910 --> 30:52.630
- [GUITAR CRASHING]
- [CROWD LAUGHING]

30:56.150 --> 30:57.584
Is he in the band?

30:57.670 --> 30:59.468
Left thumb says...

30:59.870 --> 31:01.907
Right thumb says...

31:03.030 --> 31:06.102
Aw, man, it's unanimous.

31:07.190 --> 31:10.342
I think we're gonna take
a "Passadena" on this one.

31:11.350 --> 31:12.386
[LEAVES RUSTLING]

31:13.710 --> 31:15.064
[GRUNTS]

31:16.350 --> 31:17.545
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

31:19.190 --> 31:20.226
Hey.

31:21.230 --> 31:22.869
Sorry about Trey.

31:22.990 --> 31:25.380
Yeah, you know,
don't let him go harshing your...

31:25.470 --> 31:27.780
Whoa! Where'd these come from?

31:27.870 --> 31:30.260
Um, you've had them. The whole time.

31:30.430 --> 31:33.070
Uh, this is Germur. Hey, Germ? Germur?

31:33.390 --> 31:35.507
Okay, well he's, you know,
he comes and goes.

31:35.870 --> 31:38.180
- I'm Darma. [CHUCKLES]
- Bodi.

31:38.670 --> 31:41.868
- I was so sure this was the band.
- Hey, you're gonna find one.

31:42.230 --> 31:44.347
It doesn't just happen overnight,
you know.

31:44.590 --> 31:47.230
I mean, we've been playing
in this park for, like, years.

31:47.390 --> 31:53.421
Wow. Mr. Scattergood sure made it sound
easy on the old magic singing box.

31:53.510 --> 31:55.183
The... magic... singing box?

31:55.270 --> 31:57.501
Yeah. Fell out of the sky. Almost hit me.

31:57.590 --> 31:58.660
Oh!

31:58.830 --> 32:00.344
- That happened to you, too?
- BODI: Yeah.

32:00.470 --> 32:01.460
My brother.

32:01.550 --> 32:03.542
I'm... I'm sorry. Did I hear you guys?

32:03.630 --> 32:07.544
You guys are talking about
Angus. Scattergood.

32:07.630 --> 32:08.666
Yeah?

32:08.750 --> 32:10.707
Well, did you know that the dude
lives here in town?

32:10.790 --> 32:12.622
- Really?
- Whoa, whoa, whoa! [GRUNTS]

32:13.630 --> 32:15.303
I think you ought to go up and meet him.

32:15.390 --> 32:17.188
In fact, I insist that you do.

32:17.390 --> 32:20.701
Ask him to give you some guitar lessons.
You could use them.

32:20.790 --> 32:22.986
Oh, no. No, no. You can't just go talk

32:23.070 --> 32:24.470
- to Angus Scattergood...
- Oh, sure he can.

32:24.550 --> 32:28.430
You march on up there,
big old white house on top of the hill,

32:28.510 --> 32:31.264
can't miss it,
and you tell him old Trey sent you.

32:31.350 --> 32:33.910
Well, okay!
I've always wanted to meet him.

32:33.990 --> 32:35.026
And one more thing!

32:35.510 --> 32:38.947
Don't forget to kiss the gate!
It's good luck!

32:39.030 --> 32:41.750
Kiss the gate, got it! Thanks!

32:43.310 --> 32:45.108
[LAUGHING]

32:49.310 --> 32:50.346
What?

32:51.790 --> 32:55.670
TOUR GUIDE: [ON PA] And to your right is
the home of rock legend Angus Scattergood.

32:55.870 --> 32:58.146
Each year, thousands of wannabe musicians

32:58.230 --> 33:00.745
flock to these gates
in the hope of meeting him,

33:00.830 --> 33:03.106
only to have their dreams crushed.

33:03.190 --> 33:05.182
Oh, look, here comes one now.

33:09.510 --> 33:12.389
Moving on to our next stop...

33:13.870 --> 33:14.906
[SNIFFS]

33:15.350 --> 33:17.182
For good luck...

33:18.110 --> 33:19.749
- [ELECTRICITY CRACKLES]
- [BOTH GASP]

33:19.830 --> 33:20.866
[DOORBELL RINGS]

33:21.670 --> 33:23.263
- Whoa!
- Oh!

33:24.910 --> 33:27.186
- [GLASS SHATTERS]
- Oh! [GROANS]

33:28.910 --> 33:29.946
##

33:38.030 --> 33:40.261
IAN: [OVER PHONE] Angus!
How can the label release

33:40.350 --> 33:42.342
your new song if
you haven't given it to us?

33:42.510 --> 33:44.229
- ANGUS: Ian. Ian. Ian, man. Ian.
- We've given you more time...

33:44.310 --> 33:45.505
- IAN: What?
- It's done.

33:45.630 --> 33:47.030
Then send it now!

33:47.110 --> 33:48.146
ANGUS: There's a tweaky-tweak
I have to do.

33:48.230 --> 33:49.823
IAN: You've been tweaking for six months!

33:49.910 --> 33:52.505
Yeah, well, you know, I'd be finished now
if you didn't keep ringing me.

33:52.590 --> 33:54.900
IAN: I'm ringing you because
you are in very deep trouble, Angus!

33:54.990 --> 33:56.902
- [HUFFS]
- IAN: Well, we're going to stick by you.

33:56.990 --> 33:58.868
- For now.
- Oh, for now?

33:58.950 --> 34:00.430
That sounds like a threat, Ian.

34:00.670 --> 34:02.627
A threat of violence. And murder.

34:02.710 --> 34:05.464
IAN: Oh, It's a threat!
You're down to three days to turn this in.

34:05.550 --> 34:07.781
Well, I don't need three days, mate...
Well, actually I do.

34:07.870 --> 34:10.590
IAN:
If you don't deliver, we are dropping you.

34:10.670 --> 34:12.946
And you will soon be eating
out of a dumpster!

34:13.030 --> 34:15.340
Don't you be down on dumpsters.
I grew up in one.

34:15.429 --> 34:17.864
- IAN: Angus...
- Just... just chill the fudge cake out.

34:17.949 --> 34:20.670
All right? It's all cool.
I'm gonna hang up on you now. All right?

34:20.750 --> 34:23.025
- Angus! You don't talk to me like that!
- Okay! Gotta do tweaking.

34:23.110 --> 34:24.942
- IAN: You listen to me, don't hang...
- [LINE DISCONNECTS]

34:26.750 --> 34:27.786
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

34:28.670 --> 34:30.706
How am I going to write a song
in three days?

34:30.830 --> 34:31.820
[PHONE BEEPING]

34:31.909 --> 34:33.389
Yesterday I had four days,
before that I had five days.

34:33.469 --> 34:34.824
Now I've got three days?

34:35.270 --> 34:36.590
All right,
you've got to pull yourself together.

34:36.710 --> 34:37.860
Pull yourself together. [MUTTERING]

34:39.110 --> 34:41.181
You are a rock god. I am not a rock god.

34:41.270 --> 34:43.989
Yes, you are a rock god.
Everyone thinks you're a rock god.

34:45.270 --> 34:48.103
So we must rock. We must rock.

34:49.389 --> 34:50.426
[MUSIC PLAYING]

34:52.510 --> 34:53.989
ANNOUNCER: Ladies and gentlemen,

34:54.070 --> 34:59.225
put your hands together
for the rock legend you came to see,

34:59.310 --> 35:02.701
- Angus Scattergood!
- [CROWD CHEERING]

35:02.790 --> 35:04.144
[WHIRRING]

35:05.830 --> 35:07.628
[GUITAR MUSIC PLAYING]

35:13.830 --> 35:15.867
[GRUNTING]

35:24.910 --> 35:26.629
- [GRUNTS]
- [ELECTRICITY CRACKLES]

35:28.150 --> 35:29.743
[GROANS]

35:30.990 --> 35:33.221
[WHIRRING, BEEPS]

35:40.470 --> 35:42.223
- [BEEPING]
- Whoa!

35:45.750 --> 35:46.979
[PANTING]

35:59.830 --> 36:00.946
- [GRUNTING]
- [BEEPING]

36:01.110 --> 36:03.022
[SCREAMS] Phew!

36:05.990 --> 36:07.549
- [LAUGHS]
- [MECHANICAL BEEPING]

36:08.190 --> 36:09.544
- [GASPS]
- [CAMERA WHIRRING]

36:10.070 --> 36:11.424
[GASPS]

36:12.390 --> 36:14.382
Oh, boy.

36:14.790 --> 36:16.861
[DISTANT GUITAR MUSIC PLAYING]

36:23.910 --> 36:25.344
[GRUNTS]

36:26.710 --> 36:28.144
[METAL CLANGS]

36:31.430 --> 36:33.308
Let's have some of that champagne then,
Ozzy!

36:33.390 --> 36:34.380
Right.

36:34.470 --> 36:35.506
[TAPE WHIRRING]

36:36.190 --> 36:37.226
Here we go.

36:38.590 --> 36:40.786
[GUITAR MUSIC PLAYING ON HEADPHONES]

36:48.910 --> 36:51.061
Why can't... Rubbish!

36:51.590 --> 36:54.947
Mother... father... [GRUNTING]

36:59.270 --> 37:00.909
[DOORBELL RINGING]

37:01.430 --> 37:02.750
Huh?

37:10.190 --> 37:12.466
[DOORBELL RINGING]

37:14.590 --> 37:17.059
ANGUS: [OVER INTERCOM] Stop that!
You're giving me a bloody headache!

37:17.150 --> 37:18.140
Oh, me?

37:18.230 --> 37:21.189
ANGUS: No, the other monkey
who's pressing the doorbell.

37:21.270 --> 37:23.785
- Yes, you, you big twit!
- Are you Mr. Scattergood?

37:23.870 --> 37:26.704
ANGUS: No. I am his, uh... butler.

37:26.790 --> 37:29.988
Mr. Scattergood is indisposed
at the moment.

37:30.070 --> 37:31.584
One quick question, Mr. Butler.

37:31.990 --> 37:33.788
If you could just ask Mr. Scattergood

37:34.590 --> 37:37.025
if he'd be interested
in becoming my music teacher?

37:37.110 --> 37:38.430
See there's this band and they're really...

37:38.510 --> 37:39.660
ANGUS: Did you say music teacher?

37:39.750 --> 37:40.820
- BODI: Yes, sir.
- ANGUS: Is this...

37:40.910 --> 37:41.946
Just hang on a moment.

37:43.230 --> 37:44.266
[ANGUS LAUGHING IN THE DISTANCE]

37:46.790 --> 37:49.180
We've just got news
through my headpiece here

37:49.270 --> 37:51.387
that Mr. Scattergood
would love nothing more

37:51.470 --> 37:52.790
than to be your music teacher.

37:52.910 --> 37:56.460
[LAUGHS] What? That... That is incredible.

37:56.550 --> 37:59.384
Thank you so much.
Today's my lucky day, Mr. Butler!

37:59.470 --> 38:01.223
- ANGUS: It must be.
- [BODI GROANS]

38:01.310 --> 38:04.462
ANGUS: But we've got certain conditions,
mate, certain conditions. Uh...

38:04.550 --> 38:06.030
You've got to wipe your feet
before you come in.

38:06.110 --> 38:07.464
You got it.

38:09.790 --> 38:12.066
ANGUS: Could you wipe them
specifically on the welcome mat?

38:12.150 --> 38:14.187
Otherwise you're just
moving dirt around, mate.

38:14.270 --> 38:15.306
Okay, I'll just...

38:15.990 --> 38:17.026
[SCREAMING]

38:18.190 --> 38:19.624
[GROANING]

38:23.510 --> 38:25.388
This must be a test or something, right?

38:25.990 --> 38:28.744
Mr. Scattergood said to never stop!

38:28.830 --> 38:30.981
- And nothing will ever make me...
- [LIGHTNING CRACKLING]

38:33.670 --> 38:36.902
Oh, boy.

38:39.950 --> 38:42.067
Okay, new plan!

38:42.150 --> 38:45.826
I'm gonna stay in this shelter
until the rain passes!

38:45.910 --> 38:48.470
And then we'll talk
about those music lessons!

38:49.190 --> 38:53.548
- [MECHANICAL WHIRRING]
- BODI: Whoa!

38:53.630 --> 38:56.350
Whoa! What's happening?
Hey, hey where are we going?

38:56.470 --> 38:57.506
See that, Ozzy?

38:58.430 --> 39:02.390
That was a nutter.
We won't be seeing his like again.

39:05.950 --> 39:06.827
##

39:17.630 --> 39:19.428
[BOTH GRUNTING]

39:20.390 --> 39:21.426
[LAUGHS]

39:21.950 --> 39:23.225
CROCODILE: Woo-wee!

39:23.310 --> 39:25.506
Smoked that feller! Who's next?

39:25.670 --> 39:28.583
I like this guy. Put him in the ring
tomorrow with the Grizz.

39:28.710 --> 39:31.350
Huh! No, no, not the Grizz.

39:31.430 --> 39:35.549
Anything but the Grizz.
[SOBS] Anything but the Grizz!

39:35.870 --> 39:38.544
You go in there, you don't come out!

39:38.830 --> 39:40.264
I'm gonna meet my gator-maker!

39:41.190 --> 39:42.909
Nice. Thank you.

39:43.710 --> 39:45.349
LINNUX: [OVER PHONE]
So where's the mastiff?

39:45.430 --> 39:46.705
It didn't come together.

39:46.790 --> 39:50.306
LINNUX: Didn't come together?
What is this, a jigsaw puzzle?

39:50.390 --> 39:53.349
A standard kidnapping
is too much for you two?

39:53.430 --> 39:56.582
Well, we were this close,
but he gave Skozz the slip.

39:56.670 --> 39:57.990
[STAMMERING]

39:58.070 --> 39:59.140
Yeah, that guy's crafty.

39:59.230 --> 40:00.380
Okay, you knuckleheads,

40:00.590 --> 40:03.901
you're going to scour every square inch
of this city. Eyes peeled.

40:04.310 --> 40:06.347
I don't want you to blink
until you find him.

40:06.790 --> 40:08.907
- You know what? I'm not blinking already.
- [LINE DISCONNECTS]

40:08.990 --> 40:11.744
Hello? Hello? [SIGHS]

40:12.950 --> 40:14.430
What, you didn't get one for me?

40:15.790 --> 40:17.270
That's messed up, Skozz.

40:25.790 --> 40:28.464
[HUMMING]

40:30.310 --> 40:31.346
[GASPS]

40:31.590 --> 40:33.309
[HUMMING]

40:37.550 --> 40:40.224
[HUMMING CONTINUES]

40:42.150 --> 40:43.186
[GRUNTS]

40:46.590 --> 40:47.626
[TAPE SCRATCHING]

40:48.270 --> 40:50.387
..what? None of this stuff works!

40:50.830 --> 40:52.583
- [CONTINUES HUMMING]
- [WHIRRING]

40:59.150 --> 41:00.709
[PANTING, EXHALES DEEPLY]

41:03.830 --> 41:04.866
Okay.

41:05.070 --> 41:06.060
[GUITAR MUSIC PLAYING OUTSIDE]

41:06.150 --> 41:07.948
[BODI MUFFLED] # Garbage truck #

41:08.030 --> 41:09.066
[GASPS]

41:09.150 --> 41:10.982
BODI: # I took a ride in a garbage truck #

41:11.070 --> 41:12.265
[GRUNTS]

41:14.390 --> 41:15.426
[SCATTING]

41:17.190 --> 41:18.510
Don't listen, don't listen.

41:18.790 --> 41:20.747
- [HUMMING]
- [BODI SINGING INDISTINCTLY OUTSIDE]

41:21.590 --> 41:22.865
[HUFFS]

41:24.110 --> 41:25.146
[EXCLAIMS, GRUNTS]

41:25.950 --> 41:26.986
[BODI SINGING]

41:28.110 --> 41:30.181
# I took a ride in a garbage truck #

41:30.670 --> 41:31.990
Shut up that bloody racket!

41:32.350 --> 41:35.104
# Oh, I took a ride in a garbage truck #

41:35.190 --> 41:38.342
[VOCALZING]

41:38.430 --> 41:40.706
- [MECHANICAL WHIRRING]
- [BODI HUMMING]

41:43.350 --> 41:44.500
# Yeah, I took a ride in it #

41:44.590 --> 41:47.185
# You know it's true hey hey hey #

41:47.270 --> 41:49.739
Did you bloody hear me?
You are doing my nut in!

41:49.830 --> 41:53.267
I was this close to laying down
a completely killer track and you...

41:53.350 --> 41:55.103
Are you Angus Scattergood?

41:55.230 --> 41:56.789
- [HORN HONKING]
- No, I'm his... gardener.

41:56.870 --> 41:57.906
Oh, my gosh!

41:58.270 --> 42:01.069
I'm actually meeting
Angus Scattergood's... gardener!

42:01.430 --> 42:04.423
- This is so... Sorry.
- Let go of me, you stupid mutt.

42:04.990 --> 42:07.346
Sorry. Could you give Mr. Scattergood
a message from me?

42:07.430 --> 42:08.910
I'll give him a message, all right!

42:08.990 --> 42:11.141
Oh, I will tell
Mr. Scattergood all about you!

42:11.270 --> 42:14.900
But he will never ever
be your music teacher!

42:14.990 --> 42:16.583
You can be sure about that, 'cause you...

42:16.710 --> 42:18.986
- Mr. Gardener
- are an idiot and you make all this...

42:19.070 --> 42:21.460
- [SCREAMS] The gates are closing!
- [ELECTRICITY CRACKLING]

42:21.590 --> 42:22.660
- [ANGUS SCREAMING]
- [BOTH GASPING]

42:22.750 --> 42:24.184
- [GRUNTS]
- [DOORBELL RINGING]

42:24.590 --> 42:26.821
- [OBJECTS CLATTERING]
- [THUDDING]

42:29.550 --> 42:31.030
- [GLASS SQUEAKING]
- [GROANING]

42:31.750 --> 42:32.786
[BLUBBERING]

42:34.430 --> 42:36.023
Are you all right, Mr. Gardener?
Here, let me help you.

42:36.110 --> 42:38.864
Don't you come near me, you weirdo.

42:38.950 --> 42:39.986
Ozzy!

42:40.430 --> 42:43.025
[MUSIC PLAYING ON TELEVISION]

42:44.830 --> 42:46.344
Bring round the golf cart, mate.

42:47.190 --> 42:50.627
I have been zapped by the doodah.

42:51.190 --> 42:56.868
I'm completely paralyzed, Ozzy!
Except for my mouth.

42:57.390 --> 42:59.746
My mouth is where... And my finger.

43:00.110 --> 43:03.148
TOUR GUIDE: [ON PA] And to your right
is the home of rock legend...

43:04.190 --> 43:05.180
- Angus Scattergood!
- [TOURISTS CHATTERING EXCITEDLY]

43:05.270 --> 43:07.341
It's him! It's Angus Scattergood!

43:07.470 --> 43:10.429
This is all your fault, you big, daft...

43:10.510 --> 43:14.026
I can walk! I can walk! It's a miracle!

43:14.110 --> 43:15.829
[TOURIST EXCLAIMING]

43:15.910 --> 43:16.946
##

43:23.350 --> 43:24.500
[RECORD STORE CROWD EXCLAIMING]

43:25.830 --> 43:27.549
[LAUGHS]
Wow, there's a lot of people back there.

43:27.630 --> 43:28.666
Don't you run with me.

43:28.750 --> 43:29.900
Why are they all chasing us?

43:29.990 --> 43:32.300
Because I...
because I am Angus Scattergood!

43:32.390 --> 43:35.269
Whoa! What?
I knew you were Angus Scattergood!

43:35.350 --> 43:38.149
Hey, what do you think about
maybe becoming my music teacher?

43:38.230 --> 43:39.380
I'm not going to be
your music teacher, mate!

43:39.470 --> 43:41.746
- Will you just think about it?
- Look, when I count to three,

43:41.830 --> 43:44.140
you go off to the right
and I'll carry on in this direction, okay?

43:44.230 --> 43:49.350
- One, two, three.
- Okay.

43:49.470 --> 43:50.460
Can't do it.

43:50.550 --> 43:52.781
- You're still following me, you big twit!
- I'm gonna stick with you.

43:54.510 --> 43:55.910
[PANTING]

43:59.550 --> 44:01.985
- [TOURISTS EXCLAIMING]
- I'm you're number one fan!

44:04.350 --> 44:05.386
[GARBAGE CLATTERING]

44:06.390 --> 44:08.347
BODI: I think they're gone.

44:11.230 --> 44:12.266
[GASPS]

44:13.110 --> 44:16.387
Got to get the germs off.
Dirt and germs. [GRUNTS]

44:17.150 --> 44:18.186
Ah!

44:19.150 --> 44:22.143
Ah, ooh, ah, ooh, ah! [SPITTING]

44:22.990 --> 44:25.585
This is a nightmare.
I want to be back at my castle.

44:25.870 --> 44:29.784
With my duvet. I'm cold.
I'm hungry, and I'm...

44:29.950 --> 44:30.986
[GULPING]

44:31.230 --> 44:32.744
- Never going to eat pizza again.
- Wow!

44:33.110 --> 44:34.146
Are you sure about that?

44:34.230 --> 44:36.904
Because there's plenty of food in here.
It's really good.

44:36.990 --> 44:40.142
Eating food in a dumpster.
Eating food in a dumpster.

44:40.270 --> 44:41.863
This is what he said would happen.

44:42.030 --> 44:45.706
Isn't life funny?
I mean, here I am with Angus Scattergood.

44:45.790 --> 44:48.305
Yeah, I know I said
I was Angus Scattergood,

44:48.390 --> 44:50.586
but I was just mucking about
with you really 'cause I'm...

44:50.670 --> 44:51.706
[OBJECTS CLATTERING]

44:51.830 --> 44:52.900
Mother.

44:53.230 --> 44:55.699
- Why'd they have to use that photo?
- Great picture.

44:55.830 --> 44:58.299
- Nah, I don't...
- Such a cool picture.

44:58.390 --> 44:59.380
I did not sign off on that photo, so...

44:59.470 --> 45:01.621
- Okay, I'm just going to quickly hug you.
- No! Don't you touch me!

45:01.750 --> 45:04.504
I heard you on the magic box
and you changed my life!

45:04.630 --> 45:07.145
[GRUMBLING]
Well, you have quite ruined mine, mate.

45:07.230 --> 45:09.222
So you know what? Just...

45:09.310 --> 45:12.986
Just give us a fiver for a cab,
and we'll call it quits, all right?

45:13.070 --> 45:15.141
Yeah? A fiver? Just...

45:15.230 --> 45:17.142
You lend me five of them.
Five of the one things.

45:17.230 --> 45:19.301
Oh, money? Yeah! No.

45:19.390 --> 45:22.349
No, I know where we can get money, yeah.
Lots of it.

45:22.550 --> 45:26.100
[GUITAR MUSIC PLAYING]

45:28.630 --> 45:29.666
[COIN CLINKING]

45:30.310 --> 45:32.620
Hey, Mr. Scattergood! We made a penny!

45:33.270 --> 45:37.105
Shh! Don't you understand
what "incognito" means?

45:37.590 --> 45:39.821
Um, just a button. Wasn't a penny.

45:39.910 --> 45:41.264
Sorry about that, Mr. Scattergood.

45:41.350 --> 45:43.103
Don't use the name!

45:43.310 --> 45:45.461
Just make me enough for a cab fare,
all right?

45:45.550 --> 45:46.779
BODI: Sure thing, got it.

45:47.270 --> 45:49.466
- [GUITAR MUSIC PLAYING]
- [HORN HONKING]

45:58.630 --> 45:59.666
RIFF: Bingo!

45:59.750 --> 46:01.150
We got him this time.

46:01.270 --> 46:04.183
Come on, Skozz, let's go pull around
the back. Woo-hoo-hoo!

46:04.910 --> 46:07.027
All right, how much have you made so far?

46:07.150 --> 46:08.140
Just a button.

46:08.430 --> 46:09.420
Just a button?

46:09.830 --> 46:11.867
Yep. One button.
It's a good start, though.

46:13.230 --> 46:15.506
Give me that swamp fiddle thing.

46:15.710 --> 46:16.985
[TUNES GUITAR]

46:17.670 --> 46:19.627
[GUITAR PLAYING]

46:21.630 --> 46:23.189
Can you give me a bit of space here?

46:23.310 --> 46:24.380
- Oh.
- Just back up a bit.

46:24.470 --> 46:25.699
- How's this?
- ANGUS: Bit further.

46:25.790 --> 46:28.669
- Okay, how 'bout now?
- Another 20 steps back.

46:30.670 --> 46:31.899
Get in the hedge.

46:32.830 --> 46:34.105
BODI: I can't see you!

46:34.190 --> 46:35.226
Perfect!

46:36.110 --> 46:38.750
Second time's a charm! [LAUGHS]

46:39.990 --> 46:42.459
- DARMA: Bodi?
- Oh, hey, Darma.

46:42.630 --> 46:43.859
Are you okay?

46:43.950 --> 46:47.068
Yeah, yeah. I've just been, uh,
hanging out with Mr. Scattergood.

46:47.190 --> 46:48.510
Whoa, whoa! Sorry. Back up.

46:49.110 --> 46:53.070
You've been hanging with rock legend,
Angus Scattergood?

46:53.230 --> 46:54.983
- Uh, yup.
- GERMUR: Right on.

46:55.190 --> 46:58.103
- Hanging with Angus.
- He was not hanging.

46:58.190 --> 46:59.465
Hangus with Angus.

46:59.550 --> 47:02.270
Really. We've been together all day.

47:02.350 --> 47:03.386
Let's see...

47:03.990 --> 47:05.026
We went jogging.

47:05.270 --> 47:07.068
- Then we had some pizza.
- DARMA: Right.

47:07.150 --> 47:08.470
- [ANGUS YELLING]...hey! Come on!
- Then we came here to the park 'cause,

47:08.550 --> 47:10.542
you know, he needs a little money
for a cab.

47:10.670 --> 47:11.660
- Of course.
- ANGUS: Help me! Help me!

47:11.750 --> 47:13.264
He's right over there.
You guys want to meet him?

47:13.350 --> 47:14.704
Yeah. Yeah, we do.

47:14.790 --> 47:17.942
Yes, that's a great idea.
Let's all just go meet Angus!

47:18.030 --> 47:20.704
- Sweet! We're meeting Angus!
- Don't get your hopes up.

47:20.950 --> 47:24.910
[YELLING] Oi! You big twit.
Hey! What's going on...

47:25.190 --> 47:26.260
[YELLS]

47:27.310 --> 47:30.189
And here he is, Mr.... Mr. Scattergood?

47:30.470 --> 47:34.510
Woo-wee! We did it! We did it!

47:37.390 --> 47:39.029
He was right here.
I don't know what happened.

47:39.110 --> 47:40.624
I don't know where he went.

47:40.710 --> 47:42.588
- I believe you, dog.
- You do?

47:43.390 --> 47:45.268
I do what? What do I do?

47:45.350 --> 47:50.106
Look, Bodi, you know, you don't have
to make stuff up to impress us.

47:50.190 --> 47:53.342
What? No, no. He was right here.
I gotta find him.

47:53.630 --> 47:56.190
Mr. Scattergood! Where are you?

47:56.350 --> 47:58.819
- Mr. Scattergood! Hey! Where'd you go?
- Oh...

47:58.910 --> 48:01.061
- He's cute.
- BODI: We wanted to hangus!

48:01.150 --> 48:03.790
Completely delusional, but cute.

48:04.910 --> 48:05.946
[TIRES SCREECHING]

48:07.430 --> 48:09.467
Boom! Mission accomplished!

48:10.070 --> 48:11.743
Hmm...

48:11.830 --> 48:12.866
[WOLVES CHUCKLING]

48:13.750 --> 48:14.786
[LINNUX LAUGHING]

48:15.070 --> 48:16.106
You got the goods?

48:16.230 --> 48:18.540
- We got the goods.
- [LAUGHING]

48:19.670 --> 48:21.150
[SNARLING]

48:26.150 --> 48:30.030
You kidnapped Angus flipping Scattergood?

48:30.110 --> 48:32.102
Angus... flip... What? He grabbed the guy!

48:32.190 --> 48:34.421
You didn't even get the right species!

48:34.510 --> 48:35.864
WOLF: Riff, don't you know the difference?

48:35.950 --> 48:37.145
LINNUX: Is it that tough?

48:37.870 --> 48:39.543
[WOLVES CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY]

48:39.950 --> 48:41.350
- WOLF 2: What do you expect from Riff?
- [WHISTLES]

48:42.070 --> 48:46.906
Shut up! Just shut up!
Who's in charge here? You? Large lad?

48:46.990 --> 48:49.107
I will call you... "Large Lad."

48:49.230 --> 48:51.825
You stupid, bloody idiot,
you know who I am?

48:51.950 --> 48:54.306
You're in a lot of trouble, mate.
And the entire world

48:54.750 --> 48:58.505
is going to be beating down your door
like... like salmon

48:58.590 --> 49:01.788
trying to go up a... a stream
when it's mating season.

49:01.870 --> 49:03.702
- Not a good analogy. Anyway. Look, just...
- [THUMPS]

49:05.470 --> 49:08.224
You know what?
You two morons just lost your health plan.

49:08.310 --> 49:09.869
And your 401Ks.

49:09.950 --> 49:12.385
And if you don't bring in that mastiff
by the end of the week,

49:12.470 --> 49:15.827
I'm relocating you to new digs
with bottom-of-the-oceanfront views.

49:15.910 --> 49:17.867
- Am I clear?
- Bottom of the oceanfront, got it.

49:17.950 --> 49:19.430
Now get outta my sight.

49:19.550 --> 49:21.667
Give Mr. Scattergood a ride home.

49:24.710 --> 49:29.944
Ooh! When I get ahold of your kid,
you're not going to know what hit you.

49:30.430 --> 49:31.864
- [INDISTINCT CHATTER]
- What the...

49:31.950 --> 49:33.748
- I know that was you, Feng!
- FENG: Sorry.

49:33.830 --> 49:37.585
Ethel, the headpiece goes on last
so you can see what you're doing.

49:37.670 --> 49:40.185
Come on. Guys, we've been through this.

49:40.430 --> 49:41.625
No. I... I... I think that's...

49:41.710 --> 49:44.225
I think that's a foreleg you have
on your hind leg there, Steve.

49:44.310 --> 49:46.381
- It's a left.
- STEVE: This one?

49:46.470 --> 49:47.460
The one... Left.

49:47.550 --> 49:49.109
- No. The other left.
- Oh. This one?

49:49.190 --> 49:50.829
- Oh, my goodness. Hey, Phil. Phil!
- [GRUNTING]

49:51.030 --> 49:53.101
Stop distracting Carl.
He's trying to get dressed.

49:54.190 --> 49:56.864
Wait a minute.
Carl, will you get out of the shower?

49:56.950 --> 49:59.590
- CARL: But... But I like it in here.
- I don't care, Carl.

49:59.670 --> 50:00.660
- It's time to go to work.
- [GARGLING]

50:00.750 --> 50:03.345
Come on, you're wasting time.
And water. [GRUNTS]

50:04.550 --> 50:05.586
[GROANS]

50:06.390 --> 50:08.905
We... Are...
Are you even capable of holding still?

50:08.990 --> 50:10.583
SHEEP 2: Why isn't Bodi here?

50:10.670 --> 50:14.107
For the nine billionth time,
he went to the city.

50:14.230 --> 50:16.426
- ALL: What?
- When did this happen?

50:16.510 --> 50:17.785
Do you really not remember?

50:18.350 --> 50:20.785
You gave him a going away party,
for crying out loud.

50:21.230 --> 50:23.108
[SHEEP GROUP AGREEING]

50:23.670 --> 50:26.549
- When's he coming back?
- [GROANS] Uh...

50:27.270 --> 50:28.909
I wish I knew.

50:30.750 --> 50:32.070
[ENGINE REVVING]

50:36.070 --> 50:37.902
ANGUS: Oh!

50:39.070 --> 50:40.470
[GROANING]

50:45.510 --> 50:48.662
You know what kind of a fool you made me
look like back there? Hmm?

50:51.670 --> 50:55.346
We supposed to be a team, Skozz.
We supposed to be a team.

50:57.990 --> 50:59.629
I know you hear me.

51:01.270 --> 51:04.707
I know you hear me sayin' words,
you just trying to ignore me.

51:04.790 --> 51:06.270
And I know you understand what...

51:06.790 --> 51:08.668
You playin' a video game
when I'm trying to...

51:08.750 --> 51:10.867
- Gimme that old video game!
- [VIDEO GAME BEEPING]

51:10.950 --> 51:13.306
- [HORN HONKING]
- [TIRES SCREECHING]

51:14.830 --> 51:16.344
- [BOTH GRUNTING]
- [TRUCK BEEPING]

51:16.430 --> 51:17.420
[BOTH SCREAMING]

51:19.950 --> 51:21.942
- Yeah! Whoo!
- Sweet!

51:22.350 --> 51:24.148
Put your seatbelt on, Skozz!

51:32.230 --> 51:34.870
RIFF: You can't just be doin'
whatever you want all willy-nilly.

51:34.950 --> 51:36.543
You got to do what I say.

51:36.950 --> 51:39.510
This is my last shot
at getting in good with Linnux.

51:39.590 --> 51:41.183
And you got to help me.

51:42.190 --> 51:43.590
You got anything to say?

51:45.230 --> 51:47.540
[NOTES PLAYING OFF-KEY]

51:51.430 --> 51:52.466
[PHONE RINGING]

51:52.910 --> 51:56.142
Ozzy! [EXHALES DEEPLY]
Take a message, will you?

51:58.430 --> 51:59.546
IAN: [OVER PHONE] Hello?

51:59.990 --> 52:01.219
- Angus?
- No!

52:01.310 --> 52:02.346
Angus!

52:02.510 --> 52:04.263
- Angus!
- [GRUNTS] What?

52:04.350 --> 52:05.830
IAN: Okay, where is it, Angus?

52:06.190 --> 52:08.750
I need more time, Ian.
I just... I need... I was just kidnapped.

52:08.830 --> 52:10.230
- You were not.
- I was!

52:10.310 --> 52:11.983
- They hoovered me over a wall.
- IAN: Really?

52:12.070 --> 52:14.665
They hit me with bats!
Not flying bats, but the...

52:14.750 --> 52:17.584
IAN: Oh, will you quit making lame
excuses and just get the song to us?

52:17.670 --> 52:19.866
These are some of the best excuses
I've ever had!

52:20.110 --> 52:23.660
- Just don't... Don't make me beg.
- IAN: I'm not making you beg.

52:23.750 --> 52:25.070
- Give me a bit more time...
- We already have.

52:25.150 --> 52:27.062
- Just a little bit more time...
- Tomorrow, 6:00 p.m. sharp! Bye.

52:27.150 --> 52:28.869
No! No! No! No! No! No! No!

52:28.990 --> 52:31.550
- No! No! No!
- [NOTES PLAYING OFF-KEY]

52:32.470 --> 52:35.110
[SINGING IN A DISTANCE]

52:38.350 --> 52:41.024
# I'm so stuck in this garbage truck #

52:41.110 --> 52:42.464
# That I can't even get myself out #

52:42.550 --> 52:43.620
ANGUS: Oh...

52:43.990 --> 52:49.110
That... is not... actually awful.

52:50.230 --> 52:51.459
It's...

52:52.710 --> 52:54.110
Okay-ish.

52:54.190 --> 52:55.783
# I'm so stuck in this garbage truck #

52:55.870 --> 52:57.145
ANGUS: That is...

52:57.230 --> 52:58.584
# I'm so stuck I want to get out

52:59.190 --> 53:00.260
# Singing... #

53:00.350 --> 53:02.228
ANGUS: Rather catchy.

53:02.670 --> 53:03.706
[VOCALIZING]

53:05.710 --> 53:08.908
[LAUGHS ] Hey! Hey! Mr. Scattergood!

53:09.230 --> 53:12.064
Yeah, it's me! Where ya been?

53:12.790 --> 53:16.306
- Whoo-hoo-hoo! [GRUNTS]
- ANGUS: Welcome.

53:16.470 --> 53:17.460
Welcome, welcome.

53:17.550 --> 53:20.748
- Uh, Bo... Bodee? Bohdee?
- Bodi, yes!

53:20.830 --> 53:23.186
- Bodi!
- I can't believe you remember my name.

53:23.270 --> 53:24.670
[LAUGHS] I can't either, mate.

53:24.750 --> 53:26.503
Now, what was it you were after?

53:26.630 --> 53:28.223
- Music lessons, yeah?
- Yes.

53:28.310 --> 53:30.905
Come. Come on in, mate.
Don't step on the welcome mat.

53:30.990 --> 53:32.868
And don't touch the door,
it's electrified.

53:37.110 --> 53:38.510
- This is Ozzy.
- Wow!

53:38.590 --> 53:40.707
- Yeah, just... Wait.
- Oh, wow!

53:41.110 --> 53:42.260
Just leave the robot alone for the moment.

53:42.350 --> 53:44.865
Hello, Ozzy! My name is Bodi!

53:44.950 --> 53:47.670
That's it... That's it, mate.
So, music lessons?

53:48.830 --> 53:49.866
BODI: Wow!

53:51.430 --> 53:53.740
Boy, I've... I've never seen
anything like this.

53:53.990 --> 53:55.822
My... My whole village could fit in here.

53:56.030 --> 53:58.022
ANGUS: Yeah, yeah, it could, mate. Yeah.

53:58.110 --> 53:59.146
What's that?

53:59.350 --> 54:00.386
That's my old tour bus.

54:01.110 --> 54:03.147
I've been to the moon
and back in that thing.

54:03.750 --> 54:06.629
And here is... Here is the library...

54:15.310 --> 54:16.824
BODI: Whoa!

54:16.910 --> 54:19.709
- Yeah.
- Mr. Scattergood.

54:19.990 --> 54:21.026
lndeedyweedy, mate.

54:21.830 --> 54:24.664
You want to be a rock musician?
You've got to have the proper ax.

54:26.390 --> 54:28.188
Just go ahead, pick one. Any one.

54:33.150 --> 54:34.345
Oh!

54:34.430 --> 54:35.466
[ETHERIAL MUSIC]

54:50.510 --> 54:51.580
Wait!

54:51.990 --> 54:55.062
Don't... Don't touch.
You see, that is a Scattercaster, you see?

54:55.150 --> 54:56.709
Only one in the entire universe.

54:57.150 --> 55:00.700
Crafted by Celtish people
from the timbers of a Viking ship

55:00.790 --> 55:04.067
and presented to Saxons
by the Romans, I think it was.

55:04.190 --> 55:06.910
- Wow!
- So not that one.

55:09.910 --> 55:12.550
- Okay. How... How 'bout that one?
- No, no. Not that one.

55:13.670 --> 55:15.866
- Well, this one I like...
- No, no. Not that one.

55:16.030 --> 55:18.386
Okay. Well,
I like the color of this one...

55:18.470 --> 55:21.224
No, no. Just...
I lost the keys to that one.

55:21.390 --> 55:22.540
Ah!

55:24.950 --> 55:26.543
- [GRUNTS]
- [OBJECTS CLATTERING]

55:29.070 --> 55:30.265
What about this one?

55:31.710 --> 55:35.420
It makes you look like a rock star.

55:35.990 --> 55:38.141
So what do we learn first?

55:38.230 --> 55:40.108
Chords? Fingering? Strumming techniques?

55:40.310 --> 55:42.666
That's boring stuff.
Really, to be honest, boring.

55:42.870 --> 55:45.863
I'll teach you that later in the lesson.
Necessary, but boring.

55:46.550 --> 55:48.542
Best to start off with songwriting.

55:48.630 --> 55:50.587
Have you ever composed?

55:51.030 --> 55:53.864
I have this one little something
about a garbage truck.

55:55.150 --> 55:56.186
Can you play it?

55:57.230 --> 55:59.142
Yeah, I can give it a shot.

56:05.070 --> 56:06.390
- [GUITAR MUSIC PLAYING]
- [BODI OFF-KEY]

56:06.470 --> 56:09.588
# I'm so stuck in this garbage truck #

56:09.710 --> 56:12.623
# I just wanna get myself out #

56:12.710 --> 56:14.667
Wait... That's good.

56:14.750 --> 56:16.264
But stop it for the moment. Ah...

56:16.630 --> 56:17.666
Waste management, mate.

56:17.750 --> 56:19.946
It's not very rock 'n' roll is it,
you see?

56:20.030 --> 56:21.020
Pardon me?

56:21.110 --> 56:24.421
You've got to write something that's going
to resonate with the masses.

56:24.670 --> 56:26.821
You mean, like, something that makes
people feel good.

56:26.910 --> 56:30.745
Yes! So reach inside yourself...
Wh... where did you come from, mate?

56:32.350 --> 56:35.900
- My... my town's called Snow Mountain.
- ANGUS: What's that make you feel like?

56:36.310 --> 56:37.426
Uh...

56:38.830 --> 56:40.583
What's the word? Uh...

56:40.670 --> 56:42.263
- Disgusted?
- No...

56:42.350 --> 56:44.387
- Uh, entrapped?
- Not really.

56:44.470 --> 56:46.109
- Angry? Bitter?
- Uh...

56:46.190 --> 56:47.385
- Judgmental?
- Not quite.

56:47.470 --> 56:48.506
- One horse?
- No.

56:48.590 --> 56:50.547
- Anti-cat?
- I got it!

56:51.470 --> 56:52.506
Glorious.

56:52.870 --> 56:56.181
Glorious? Yeah. That'll do.

56:57.230 --> 56:59.426
[GUITAR MUSIC PLAYING]

57:13.070 --> 57:16.381
[PIANO MUSIC PLAYING]

57:25.390 --> 57:27.621
[BEAT FADES IN]

57:44.830 --> 57:46.981
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYING]

57:48.910 --> 57:51.106
[CLANGING]

57:53.270 --> 57:55.182
[ELECTRIC GUITAR MUSIC PLAYING]

58:04.350 --> 58:06.103
[INAUDIBLE]

58:37.310 --> 58:38.346
[SHOCKWAVE]

58:39.510 --> 58:40.546
[OZZY EXCLAIMS]

58:40.630 --> 58:41.666
[WINDOW SHATTERS]

58:48.910 --> 58:51.425
Rock and roll, mate!

58:51.510 --> 58:52.546
[PANTING]

58:52.870 --> 58:54.827
I... I can't believe I did that.

58:54.910 --> 58:57.220
Yeah, you were on fire!

58:57.510 --> 58:59.741
That's what you were.
You were totally on fire!

58:59.830 --> 59:01.469
You were in the zone!

59:01.590 --> 59:02.944
- Did you feel it?
- I did feel it!

59:03.030 --> 59:05.750
I felt it. I felt it... You blew up my
room!

59:05.870 --> 59:06.906
You blew up my room!

59:07.070 --> 59:08.390
I'm sorry, Mr. Scattergood!

59:08.470 --> 59:10.985
It doesn't matter. It does not matter.

59:11.070 --> 59:12.584
Nothing to worry about, all right?

59:15.430 --> 59:19.140
The song... is done. It is done.

59:22.150 --> 59:24.028
BODI: So, that's the lesson?

59:24.110 --> 59:25.146
ANGUS: Yeah it is.

59:25.710 --> 59:28.544
[LAUGHING] Why, it's one of the best
I've ever given.

59:29.630 --> 59:31.064
Watch the welcome mat. There you go.

59:31.150 --> 59:32.903
So when should I come back?

59:32.990 --> 59:34.868
[FLAPS LIPS] Is that...

59:34.950 --> 59:37.181
For our second lesson? Is tomorrow good?

59:37.270 --> 59:40.786
Why, um...
that's gonna be... It's tricky, uh,

59:41.150 --> 59:44.541
really slammed stuff, you know,
on the calendar-wise, you know.

59:44.630 --> 59:47.350
But we, we could...
I'll get my people to...

59:47.470 --> 59:49.109
But, you know, we'll work out something.

59:49.190 --> 59:52.149
Okay. Well,
I guess I'll just go over to the park.

59:52.230 --> 59:54.062
- Great, great, mate. Just, uh...
- [BEEPING]

59:54.150 --> 59:55.425
hurry up before the hedge pops up....

59:57.110 --> 59:58.624
There you go, mate! Mind the mice!

59:58.710 --> 01:00:01.179
- Okay! Well, goodbye!
- Bye then!

01:00:01.350 --> 01:00:02.864
- BODI: Bye, Ozzy!
- [ANGUS MUMBLES INDISTINCTLY]

01:00:02.950 --> 01:00:05.067
- See you soon!
- [ANGUS MUMBLES INDISTINCTLY]

01:00:09.310 --> 01:00:11.506
[GRUNTING, PANTING] Whoo-hoo!

01:00:12.430 --> 01:00:15.548
Guys, you're not gonna believe this.
You're not gonna believe it!

01:00:15.630 --> 01:00:19.021
Mr. Scattergood gave me a music lesson!
And we wrote a song together!

01:00:19.110 --> 01:00:20.226
- He even let...
- GERMUR: Whoa! Hey...

01:00:20.310 --> 01:00:21.983
- RADIO DJ: On the line, right now,
- He's on! He's on!

01:00:22.070 --> 01:00:24.426
RADIO DJ OVER RADIO: Angus, tell us...
Tell us about your new single.

01:00:24.510 --> 01:00:26.103
[ANGUS OVER RADIO]
It's been a long time coming,

01:00:26.190 --> 01:00:27.544
and everyone's been saying,
"When's it coming?"

01:00:27.630 --> 01:00:29.269
And here it is, baby, out tomorrow.

01:00:29.830 --> 01:00:32.425
And it is called "Glorious."

01:00:32.510 --> 01:00:33.785
Yeah, "Glorious!"

01:00:33.870 --> 01:00:35.668
- That's the song we did!
- [ROCK PARK MUSICIANS] Shh. Shh. Quiet!

01:00:35.750 --> 01:00:37.264
RADIO DJ: So, uh, what inspired you?

01:00:37.350 --> 01:00:39.387
ANGUS: Uh, well, funny story.

01:00:39.630 --> 01:00:42.270
I was sitting in my studio
and the bell rang.

01:00:42.350 --> 01:00:44.387
- Yep. That was me.
- ANGUS: Which almost never happens.

01:00:44.470 --> 01:00:46.905
I go to the door
and there was nobody there.

01:00:47.190 --> 01:00:48.180
What?

01:00:48.270 --> 01:00:51.502
ANGUS: But I looked up,
and I thought of where I grew up.

01:00:51.630 --> 01:00:56.386
Up in the mountains where...
Uh, where the snows are.

01:00:56.510 --> 01:00:59.787
And I thought, "This is glorious, mate.
It's just glorious."

01:00:59.870 --> 01:01:02.863
And it came... came straight
from the heart.

01:01:02.950 --> 01:01:07.627
From, uh, my heart, to be clear.
That was from my heart.

01:01:07.910 --> 01:01:08.900
RADIO DJ: That's beautiful.

01:01:08.990 --> 01:01:11.380
ANGUS: Well, I'd be remiss if I didn't
acknowledge

01:01:11.510 --> 01:01:13.422
someone who was there for me,

01:01:13.510 --> 01:01:15.547
and without whom this song
would not have been written.

01:01:15.630 --> 01:01:20.386
And that person
of course is my butler, Ozzy.

01:01:20.870 --> 01:01:22.907
And he, in his own way, he is glorious.

01:01:23.590 --> 01:01:25.582
Or not glorious.
What's a better word for it?

01:01:25.750 --> 01:01:27.389
- Square-shaped.
- [STEREO CLICKS]

01:01:28.190 --> 01:01:30.386
Uh, he didn't mention you. Why not?

01:01:30.470 --> 01:01:34.066
Oh, that's right
'cause the dude doesn't know you exist!

01:01:34.150 --> 01:01:35.948
[ROCK PARK MUSICIANS LAUGHING]

01:01:38.830 --> 01:01:39.866
##

01:01:44.870 --> 01:01:46.224
Bodi...

01:01:47.990 --> 01:01:49.982
Hey, you should really get out
of the rain.

01:01:50.790 --> 01:01:54.227
Germy and I are gonna grab some noodles.
You want to come?

01:02:03.750 --> 01:02:05.230
GERMUR: I believe you, dog.

01:02:41.550 --> 01:02:42.825
- IAN: [OVER PHONE] Hello?
- ANGUS: Ian?

01:02:42.910 --> 01:02:44.105
- IAN: Yeah?
- ANGUS: Ian?

01:02:44.230 --> 01:02:45.630
- Angus, what is it now?
- ANGUS: Ian, mate? Can you hear this?

01:02:45.710 --> 01:02:46.746
IAN: What is it now?

01:02:46.830 --> 01:02:48.901
- ANGUS: Can you hear that?
- IAN: Yeah, what is that? What is that?

01:02:48.990 --> 01:02:50.265
- It's finished.
- IAN: The song... The song's finished?

01:02:50.350 --> 01:02:51.750
- Two hours to spare.
- IAN: Yes!

01:02:51.830 --> 01:02:55.028
Okay, don't move. I'm going to send
a runner over right away.

01:02:55.110 --> 01:02:57.261
We're going to pick it up.
We're going to have a big party tonight!

01:02:57.350 --> 01:03:00.343
- I'm going to rent us a hotel, okay?
- Yeah, make it two hotels, okay?

01:03:00.430 --> 01:03:03.025
- IAN: That's really not in our budget...
- Yeah, ginormous party, all right.

01:03:03.110 --> 01:03:05.147
- We can't do that... Angus?
- All right, cheers, mate.

01:03:06.070 --> 01:03:07.902
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

01:03:09.430 --> 01:03:10.659
What?

01:03:11.990 --> 01:03:13.629
Why are you looking at me like that?

01:03:15.150 --> 01:03:16.743
Is this about that daft dog?

01:03:19.510 --> 01:03:20.944
Come on, he'll be fine.

01:03:21.670 --> 01:03:23.070
He'll be fine!

01:03:24.710 --> 01:03:26.747
Look, truth is,

01:03:27.070 --> 01:03:29.301
I could've written that song
without that dog.

01:03:31.230 --> 01:03:34.906
All right, I could not have written
that song without that dog.

01:03:35.030 --> 01:03:36.066
But...

01:03:36.750 --> 01:03:39.265
It's not like I can go around
telling people the truth.

01:03:39.350 --> 01:03:41.342
I'd lose it all, man.
I'd lose the legend...

01:03:45.190 --> 01:03:46.943
Maybe I should give
him a little something,

01:03:47.030 --> 01:03:48.464
for the inspiration, yeah?

01:03:49.310 --> 01:03:50.346
Is that a good idea?

01:03:51.190 --> 01:03:54.262
Will you stop!
You're like a stone, you are!

01:03:54.590 --> 01:03:59.460
You stare at me with your big,
tin eyes and your big, tin face.

01:03:59.550 --> 01:04:01.701
You tin thing!

01:04:05.310 --> 01:04:07.427
Ozzy! That tin can.

01:04:07.710 --> 01:04:09.542
Blackmail! It's not blackmail,
is it, technically.

01:04:09.630 --> 01:04:13.260
It's a... it's a guilt trip.
Guilt trip! That's what it is.

01:04:15.230 --> 01:04:17.347
[GUITAR MUSIC PLAYING]

01:04:25.030 --> 01:04:26.669
[VEHICLE APPROACHING]

01:04:36.790 --> 01:04:37.826
[ENGINE REVS]

01:04:39.070 --> 01:04:40.743
Oh! [GRUNTS]

01:04:43.350 --> 01:04:45.990
[RIFF LAUGHING] We got you!

01:04:46.070 --> 01:04:47.470
[PANTING]

01:04:52.350 --> 01:04:54.228
[TIRES SCREECHING]

01:04:58.710 --> 01:04:59.746
[LASERS POWERING UP]

01:05:02.750 --> 01:05:03.786
[GRUNTS]

01:05:03.990 --> 01:05:05.504
[GASPS]

01:05:09.550 --> 01:05:11.189
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

01:05:14.110 --> 01:05:15.100
[GRUNTS]

01:05:16.470 --> 01:05:18.747
- Buncha idiots.
- [CELL PHONE RINGING]

01:05:19.830 --> 01:05:21.105
- Hey, Boss!
- Did you get him?

01:05:21.190 --> 01:05:23.750
Yeah, I got him! I got him right here!

01:05:24.070 --> 01:05:25.106
Everyone okay?

01:05:25.270 --> 01:05:28.024
Yeah, yeah, um, everybody is good!

01:05:28.110 --> 01:05:31.308
Don't you worry 'bout nothin'.
I am on top of...

01:05:31.750 --> 01:05:33.662
LINNUX: Riff? Riff, you there?

01:05:33.830 --> 01:05:35.787
Oh, you better not have hung up on me!

01:05:40.230 --> 01:05:43.223
Wakey, wakey. Have a nice nap?

01:05:43.390 --> 01:05:44.426
Whoa.

01:05:45.030 --> 01:05:47.545
Let's hear all about your pop's army.

01:05:47.870 --> 01:05:50.624
How many troops?
How many lines of defense?

01:05:50.750 --> 01:05:53.390
What's their combat effectiveness?

01:05:53.790 --> 01:05:59.582
Sir, if my dad knew that
I was talking to a wolf... [CHUCKLES]

01:05:59.670 --> 01:06:00.706
Oh, boy...

01:06:01.030 --> 01:06:02.225
Mum's the word, huh? [CHUCKLES]

01:06:02.310 --> 01:06:04.188
You got nothing to say?

01:06:06.670 --> 01:06:09.185
Okay. Okay.

01:06:10.830 --> 01:06:11.820
[GRUNTS]

01:06:13.590 --> 01:06:14.626
[OBJECTS CLATTERING]

01:06:14.710 --> 01:06:17.225
Not gonna talk about...

01:06:17.310 --> 01:06:20.348
[YAWNS] the sheep army.

01:06:21.510 --> 01:06:22.830
LINNUX: Sheep army?

01:06:28.350 --> 01:06:31.707
Sheep army. Sheep army. Sheep army.

01:06:32.390 --> 01:06:33.380
[GASPS]

01:06:34.710 --> 01:06:36.702
Sheep army.

01:06:38.190 --> 01:06:39.180
[LAUGHS]

01:06:40.390 --> 01:06:41.380
[SCATTERED LAUGHTER]

01:06:43.030 --> 01:06:46.580
- I can't thank you enough!
- W... what's that?

